<br>
There isn't any harm is looking at hundreds of logs with billons of hits. IF you find that there is a slight increase in critical hits at CF2 and a bit more at CF3, its perfecly reasonable to question exactly how MUCH of a difference its is, and then to break out the scientific tests to calculate it, but there is absolutly no harm in looking at trends to say, 'Hey Verant... we've looked at a few hundred hours of logs and our inital findings are that this skill is broken. Ball is in your court now, break out your scientific tests and demonstrate its working properly or correct the error.&quot;<br>
