<br>
Procs CAN go off on a miss, Criticals as far as I've seen NEVER show up on a miss(and there's no logical reason they should). <br>
<br>
Why not use that no-miss chest mentioned above for a few hours while you're asleep next and see how it turns out, and then do the same with CF2/3?<br>
<br>
Possibly while screwing with a few different sets of stat gear over a few nights of testing, VI could have done something unexpected and based CF crits off of a stat other than DEX. I doubt they would, but who knows and if it was ATK for example you would see the average rogue with CF1 critting as much as a CF2 of most other classes I would wager.<br>
<br>
Right now, it does look like CF2 is screwy with the limited sampling so far, that's no doubt, BUT with anything that is labelled as a test you vary the testbed conditions and note all the differences, otherwise it's not science. <br>
<br>
To repeat AGAIN however, if I was playing a melee class and I was planning to get CF2 I would wait to see how further testing develops if I had the points sitting in my AAXP pool ready to spend, 5 parsed logs without any noted stat variations isn't a very scientific test - Yes, you very well might be right. Hell, I'd say you likely are, BUT that doesn't mean you should cut corners on the testing - something can look fine or wrong in simple testing but when in depth testing with wide sampling is done the original theory falls apart.<br>
<br>
I'm not challenging the data presented thusfar, I'm trying to get you to make sure there's not some factor you're missing that does make it worthwhile, instead of how crappy CF2 looks atm... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utremainbladesinger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TremainBladesinger</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/25/01 3:34:52 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.theunholytrinity.org/cracks_smileys/cwm/big/firemad.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Combat Fury -- Arguably Broken - Parsing Statistics Incl</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  1) Gear doesn't matter. It doesn't matter if you're using 10 delay weapons with 40% haste, or 100 delay weapons with no haste. The PERCENTAGE of your swings that are crits will be the same <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
